
# Parents backgrounds 

Jaskier’s parents, Aurel, his mother, and Aleksy, his father were adventurers from another continent, and they collected many cool magical things in their prime time. When they finally bore their first child, Alina (Jaskier’s older sister), they realized that the adventuring life was not going to work and so they had to stop doing it. They decided to go to Goyou and start a less adventurous life there in Emmeryn to become traders of magical stuff (they moved basically 6 months, after Alina’s birth). Even though they already had quite a collection of magical items and wealth before even coming to Emmeryn, building a business and raising a child at the same time was not easy at all for them. The market for magical items area were already pretty packed, especially considering it’s Emmeryn. 

After around 7 years, the business was finally in a solid and stable state and Alina was big enough that she didn’t require as much attention as before. Aurel and Aleksy always wanted to have 2 children, and since things are more stable now, they decided it’s time to have another child, and so Jaskier was born. 

Extra details: The family lives in the shop as well, just upstairs. 

# Growing up 

Alina was always the one who seemed to be more preferred by the parents, she helped around the house much more, well-behaved, did decent in school, never really made much trouble, listened to her parents basically most of the time. Jaskier was just the exact opposite, he goes out around Chiyoda a lot, slacked in school, didn’t help much around the house, and too expressive for his own good, at least that’s what his parents would say. 

The biggest reason why he went out a lot is because he loves exploring, but not in the traditional sense. He found connecting with other people a marvelous experience, he was also intrigued about how it would be by walking in another person’s shoes. It’s like seeing the same world that he had been in, but through different eyes.  It is then more of a re-exploration of the world.  

Obviously, he did this by changing to those people he’s trying to imitate, and because of and because of this, he runs to all sort of trouble, mostly unintentional. For example, one time he pretended to be one of the shop keepers in Chiyoda, that shop keeper unfortunately had some debts, and a debt collector saw him in the street and confront him about “his” debts. Instead of changing back towards his original form, or just ran, Jaskier roleplayed as the man and even had a little argument with the debt collector. At the end he used his parents’ money to pay off this poor man’s debt. Obviously, the parents found out about it and the originally indebted man paid his parents back. But of course, this was not resolved very smoothly and a lot of yelling and disappointment was involved. 

Because of this love with exploring people, he also fell in love with theatre. He found a theatre troupe and wanted to join it. His parents didn’t really approve him of joining the theatre troupe (not exactly because they think it’s too low for Jaskier, there’s a little bit of that, but mostly because Jaskier is supposed to be doing something else, like school). So he assumed the form of a human actor that was part of a travelling theatre troupe who happened to give a performance in Chiyoda at one point. He didn’t exactly meet the actor himself, he was surrounded by crowds, so Jaskier didn’t exactly know what he was like. This was Jaskier’s second regular face (the first one is the face similar to what his parents assume). He took the name of the character that the actor played in that performance, Steve. His idea was if he joined the local troupe as Steve, there shouldn’t be any problem. 

He hung out a lot with his theatre friends, although he joined the theatre as Steve, there were a couple of people who knew that he was a changeling. His best friends at that time, Nonya, a tabaxi, and Roxie, a dragonborn. They got close together mainly because they all somewhat feel like that they don’t belong in the world, the only way that they could feel that is performing on stage. There were many times that they would talk after rehearsals all night, and Jaskier’s parents definitely not happy having their son sort of missing all night. Keep in mind that Jaskier was probably only 13. Since they were also a part of the prop team in the troupe, they might have stolen a few art and craft materials from some shop, and definitely using Jaskier’s changeling ability to their advantage. They were all little troublemakers. 

Jaskier’s relationship with his father was definitely not great. Whenever Jaskier got home late, even just a little later than he should be, he’s the one who would start complaining and more often than it should be, they start yelling at each other. But of course, that’s not exactly all in their relationship, there’s some, though few, good interactions between them. Especially when it comes to storytelling. When Jaskier was just a toddler, when he was yet to be a reckless kid, Aleksy would read him stories every night, both him and Alina. There’s always a sense of calmness that comes with Aleksy’s story telling. So, even though they fight a lot and never seemed to get along. Their interaction would become quite friendly when they start talking about story telling and discussing the stories that come with it. 

With his mother however, it was quite different. Aurel didn’t like to yell as much as Aleksy does. She would still of course complain about Jaskier’s behavior, gave him boring lectures as well, but rarely yelled, if ever. She was not as hot headed as Aleksy and Jaskier. Although she was more quiet, her presence is just more… imposing. If Aleksy and Jaskier were at it again, Aurel would just come into the room and stood there, just with her presence the two knew they should stop. Don’t get me wrong, her presence is not exactly commanding and scary, it’s more… understanding, somewhat heartwarming too? It’s hard to explain.  

In consequence, Jaskier is closer to his mother. She even had a pet name for Jaskier, she liked to call him “my dandelion”. She said Jaskier lived his life just like it, once bloomed, it would just follow where the wind would take him. She’s not entirely wrong I suppose? Her mother is also where Jaskier would confide his troubles with, well only if necessary. Should he have troubles that needed to be resolved by the parents, he would talk to his mother first. It is probable that, even though Jaskier didn’t tell her everything, she probably knew about most things. She would also be the only one who asked how things were with Jaskier, even asked about the troupe sometimes, somehow, she just knew. 

A simple way to put it is Alina inherit her parents’ rational side, while Jaskier inherited their adventurous side. But the parents don’t want Jaskier to run around like that and just sort of wanted him to chill. But he doesn’t chill.  

Parents’ side of things: they understand how Jaskier is feeling, because they were adventurer’s themselves and loved to take risks and explore the world, though differently. But now they’ve changed, they uphold stability more than adventure, so they’re really trying their best to compromise with Jaskier, but Jaskier tend to just go fuck all. So yeah… 

# Split from the family 

After having to repeat several grades, Jaskier finally graduated high school (or whatever the equivalent is) at 21 years old. His parents were quite delighted to finally see Jaskier finishing his education, although not in the most efficient way. Aleksy already prepared big things for Jaskier’s future, Aurel was sort of against the idea since they had not talked about it with Jaskier, yet concrete preparations were already done. Aleksy had this idea that Jaskier would mostly be responsible for making and finalizing deals for the family business with parties outside of Ophelia, including parties from other continents if it comes to it. What Jaskier had to do was just study business Belle for a year and he would come back and become external region manager basically. Aleksy really thought that this would be something that Jaskier would be okay with, since he has somewhat an adventurous spirit, and this position basically would allow him to travel quite a lot and meet other people. He was so sure that Jaskier would take it that he’s made mini deals with parties from Ondinne already, where Jaskier would already be able to try to take care of it, as practice. He's even got the tuition and boarding cost covered for the business school. 

When the idea was revealed to Jaskier, he was outrageous.  

“Are you finally out of your mind? Did you really just dead set my future without even talking to me? “ Jaskier yelled, Aleksy tried to reply but as he  opened her mouth Jaskier interrupted immediately, 

”What Father? You think I’m too immature to have a say on this or something? Fucking hell, are my opinions even allowed to be fucking expressed? ”Jaskier said. 

“Watch your damn mouth boy. Of course I considered what you want, everything that we try to do for you is always in the line for what’s best for you. This position would allow you to actually explore the world and meet other people, isn’t that what you damn brat want?” Aleksy finally had a chance to reply, 

“Now you think you know what I want huh? No you don’t father! You know why? You never even bothered to ask. Is this just a ruse so you finally get rid of me huh? I’m that much trouble huh?” 

“Just follow the goddamn plan and for the love of the Phoenix just follow it and I promise you won’t regret it. I already fucking paid for the tuition of the school and other fucking expensive shits. Now what you ungrateful brat has to do is just to follow GUIDED FUCKING STEPS”  

“Well I didn’t fucking ask you to do that did I?? For my whole goddamn life you never, NEVER put any weight on what I say!” 

“Well that’s because your mouth is full of shit boy, every single you said is just utterly useless” 

“Do you even care about me? Your own fucking son. Anything that I’ve done in my life is just soooo wrong in your eyes? What the fuck is up with that?” 

“Well if you had done anything that would weigh at least a fucking copper piece I would see that, but you haven’t have you. You even needed an extra 4 fucking years to finish your goddamn school, and that was the best school in Emmeryn as well.” 

…. And so the argument went on and on and it ended by Jaskier saying… 

“Well that’s fucking it! I don’t have any say in this house, not even what I would have for dinner. I can’t never be myself when I’m around you. You want me to step out of your life then alright, this regret of yours: me, is going to fuck off from this damned shop and you won’t have to see me again. And you know what I’m going to take this book just because I can. Good fucking bye” 

And that is the last time Jaskier had any interaction with the rest of the family. To really hide from his family, he assumes now his theatre persona, Steve. 

# Theatre Kid and Con artist 

Although he spent a lot of time in the streets hanging out with his friends, he’s always had money or food to come home too. He even has a butler back home that helps with the household chores, he never really had to do anything, and thus never really could do anything. There was only one place he could think of when he left his family, Nonya and Roxie’s place. They had been living together in a small crooked house in Shinagawa. Though there’s not much space in this, barely livable space, Nonya and Roxie took Jaskier in.  

This new space is not exactly fancy, in fact very far from fancy, very far from the standard that Jaskier used to live in. So, he had to make big changes in the way he lives. Well… he actually just tells Nonya and Roxie to do most chores until they complain about that to him. He is sort of the annoying housemate.  

For a living, he does the thing that he knows best, acting, still in the same local theatre troupe that he’s been in, the Golden Sun. The thing is, they’re not exactly super popular and is still beaten by other fancier and more professional troupes. After all, the Golden Sun was formed mostly just out of hobbies, and even until this time, it still was. He then had the intention to reform the troupe itself, to become more professional, market it more to the public, gain fans, etc. But the the thing is most people in the troupe only saw the golden sun as a side hustle and nothing more, most of them didn’t actually want to take this too seriously. Jaskier, being stubborn and loud as he is, eventually got the position to lead the troupe and realize his visions for the troupe, but unfortunately most of its members left. There was now only 10 people left, including him, Nonya, and Roxie. 

As the leader of the troupe, he had to manage all sort of things for the theatre. Actually, from the money that he would get from performing, he can somewhat get by, but the thing is, he still need money to also fund the troupe (for logistics and everything). So, reluctantly, he did what he is also very good at: being other people. And this time, instead of doing it for fun, he’s doing this for money, taking advantage of other people. This didn’t exactly sit right in his heart at first, but overtime he sort of made peace with it. Afterall, it was necessary, for his own good, and for the good of the troupe.  

Although he could indeed use different faces being a con artist, he found it also beneficial if he had a regular con-artist face. Especially if he wants to build a network. As mentioned, Jaskier used Steve as his usual face. But he didn’t want the face of a beautiful actor to be associated with dirty crimes, and so he decided to use another face. Zoltan. Zoltan was again took by Jaskier from a theatre performance. Zoltan was a dangerously handsome silver tongued dwarf. In the story, Zoltan, was offered by the king to rescue the princess from the hold of a dragon. Zoltan, though was strong, preferred to use his tongue than his axe. So, he ate the dragon out, just kidding, I had to say it sorry. He managed to actually persuade the dragon to let go of the princess in turn of the whole kingdom’s treasure horde, it was obviously a bluff, but Zoltan was that persuasive, even the wisdom of a dragon can’t see through it. This story left many people’s imagination in awe, including Jaskier’s. 

To help him further in his con artist career, the random book that he stole from his parents was coincidentally a book about bardic magic. Specifically of a bard school that allows one’s expression becomes the focus of the magic. He also found out that he’s rather pretty good at it, developing very fast. His background as an actor really helped with the flow of this magic. With this magic, Jaskier used inspiration and charm to ease along the deceptive process in conning. 

With the extra money that Jaskier had gained from conning, after a few years, the Golden Sun had now a somewhat respectable name among the theatric community of Emmeryn, however, still not the best one. Even after gaining more reputation, it is still necessary for Jaskier to con, as demand increases, the funding need to increase as well. Eventually, Jaskier grew tiresome of this, he didn’t want to admit it, but there’s a little place in his heart that see the Golden Sun as somewhat of a burden now. Maybe his father was right, maybe he should’ve had just taken his proposal. His father was not exactly wrong, Jaskier indeed had always dreamed of travelling and seeing more of the world, curious of what the other part of the continent could bring. He was just too angry at the time to see that, and definitely too emotional to admit that. Or not, maybe it’s just a crazy thought. 

# Full Moon (reunion with his mother) 

Of course, after Jaskier run away, his family tried to look for him. He heard about his parents asking around where he was and everything, but he just waited it out. After a few months, it didn’t seem like they were looking for him anymore. Although that was what he wanted, it felt disappointing. Maybe his family just thought it’s best to leave him, maybe the harsh realities of life would teach him a thing or two. 

After a year past the incidental family split, Jaskier received a letter, slipped through the crooked house door threshold. The cover was simple plain white, and on it was written “To my dandelion”. The letter reads 

“I know you don’t want to talk to us, and that’s okay. I hope you’re doing okay and I hope you are closer to what you are looking for in life. Should you need anything, or even just to say hi, I will be waiting in Katsushika every full moon, next to the pond of ducks surrounded by dandelions like we used to go to long ago. I promise it will just be me. I know it might be hard to believe, but we’ve all missed you 

Love, mother”. 

That pond was a memory from long ago, from when time was not filled yet with unnecessary loud arguments between Jaskier and his father. They used to go to that pond at nights when the sky was filled with stars. Jaskier was but a little boy, probably only 6 years old. The two siblings would watch their parents act out and tell grand stories that they claimed came from the stars. 

Jaskier shook himself out of reminiscing and threw the letter away. He was even mad that that letter arrived, really for no good reason. Roxie and Nonya tried to calm him down, but honestly, for the 22 years that Jaskier had been in this world (up until this point), only time and his mother could bring his temper down (well also a joint, but yeah). The very same night Jaskier couldn’t sleep, he couldn’t help but think about the letter. He now realized, or at least finally admit, that he too missed his family. He however knew for sure that he was just not ready yet, his last interactions with them was just… unimaginable to recover from. After two hours past midnight, he went back to the trash can to retrieve his letter. It was crumpled, stained, and shred a little bit. But he could still read her mother handwriting, and for now, that’s good enough. Only then, he could finally fall asleep. 

A year full of full moons have past, and for every single one that came, Jaskier was filled with anxiety. Ever since the letter arrived, and a full moon would come, he would really overthink about if he should visit his mother in Katsushika. Most months he wouldn’t even be out but there was one where he actually went to the park. He saw his mother standing just next to the pond, feeding the fat ducks, while also looking at the stars. A sight that would bring him back far into memory lane. He wanted to step closer, but when you visit good ol’ memories, you could also slip into the bad ones. He did not manage to step closer than 200 yards away from his mother. 

Another full moon is coming, he gathered all the courage to come again to the park, and off he went. Again, standing from a far, he saw his mother tending to the same fat ducks. He was really determined already to actually talk to her, or at least that’s what he thought. But his legs are just not cooperating, deep inside his subconscious mind there’s still a big fear that stopped him from moving closer. Jaskier finally just gave up, he thought to himself that I guess seeing his mother from a far is already quite heartwarming. She eventually left. 

Jaskier sighed deeply and walked to the pond. He sat where he used to as a child and stared at the ducks, who happily float around like if there was never a problem in the world. He picked a dandelion flower and just looked at it for a while, as if he was contemplating about past deeds, but actually he was just admiring the beauty of it. He spun the dandelion, and it flew off his hands. He looked back at the pond, now to see his reflection. Behind him is a flock of bright stars, lead by a big silver moon. Slowly approaching from his periphery, the same dandelion that he threw float back at him, covering the reflection of his face.  

“My Dandelion” Suddenly a familiar warm voice came from behind. 

“Did I really have to pretend to go so that you would finally come to the pond?” 

Jaskier was shocked, but his mother just smiled and gave him a hug. 

Every full moon, at the same time, at the same pond. Jaskier saw his mother regularly to catch up and have a nice little conversation. Her mother, again, weirdly knew about his con acts. After telling him about it, Jaskier expected a boring old lecture, that he weirdly missed, only to hear her mother telling him to be careful. A somewhat pleasant surprise. Really, she just wanted best for him. He’s not ready yet to see his whole family again, but this is already more than he could have ever imagined.
